[30;1m33 | [0m[35m        if (cached := cache.get(key)) is not None:[0m
[30;1m34 | [0m[35m            # Deserialize from JSON based on the return type[0m
[30;1m35 | [0m[35m            if issubclass(return_type, BaseModel):[0m
[30;1m36 | [0m[35m                return return_type.model_validate_json(cached)[0m

[30;1m113 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m114 | [0m[35mUsing `asyncio.gather` allows us to return all the results at once. It is an effective way to speed [0m
[30;1m115 | [0m[35m[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m806[0m[34m of [0m[33m1627[0m[31m ]--[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m807[0m[34m of [0m[33m1627[0m[31m ]--[0m

[30;1m186 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m187 | [0m[35mAs you can see, the `for` loop is the slowest, while `asyncio.as_completed` and `asyncio.gather` are[0m
[30;1m188 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m189 | [0m[35m| Method               | Execution Time | Rate Limited (Semaphore) |[0m
[30;1m190 | [0m[35m| -------------------- | -------------- | ------------------------ |[0m
[30;1m191 | [0m[35m| For Loop             | 6.17 seconds   |                          |[0m
[30;1m192 | [0m[35m| Asyncio.gather       | 0.85 seconds   |                          |[0m
